 browser that supports HTML5 standards and is able to display PNG images. Please try Mozilla Firefox if you encounter any problems.</td></tr><tr><td class="tbg1" align="left" valign="middle" colspan="2">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td class="tbg1" align="left" valign="middle" colspan="2">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td class="tbg1" align="left" valign="middle" colspan="2"><br />The increased amount of data submissions within the last few weeks has resulted in a negative user experience (long waiting times, jobs not finishing, etc.) due to our limitted resources. Therefore, we have decided to <b>not accept submissions to the DeconSeq web service</b> until we have updated our hardware to cope with the increase in submitted data.<br />Please refer to the standalone version available at <a target="_new" href="http://deconseq.sourceforge.net">http://deconseq.sourceforge.net</a> until the web service is accepting data again. For any questions, please refer to the Q&A site (<a href="https://groups.google.com/d/forum/edwardslabtools">https://groups.google.com/d/forum/edwardslabtools</a>). We appologize for any inconvenience this might cause.</td></tr><tr><td class="tbg1" align="left" valign="middle" colspan="2">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td class="tbg1" rowspan="1" align="left" valign="middle">&nbsp;</td></tr></table><input type="hidden" name="i" value="1"  /></form></div><div id="footerbg">2010-2013 Copyright &copy;&nbsp;Robert Schmieder&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://groups.google.com/d/forum/edwardslabtools">Q&A site</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a target="_blank" href="http://edwards.sdsu.edu/labsite">Edwards Lab @ SDSU</a></div></div></center><script type="text/javascript">var _gaq = _gaq || [];_gaq.push(['_setAccount', 'UA-1147042-2']);_gaq.push(['_trackPageview']);(function() { var ga = document.createElement('script'); ga.type = 'text/javascript'; ga.async = true;ga.src = ('https:' == document.location.protocol ? 'https://ssl' : 'http://www') + '.google-analytics.com/ga.js';var s = document.getElements